ques.p: To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions how many people were enrolled in welfare-to-work schemes (a) in total and (b) in each programme at the start of (i) 2010-11 and (ii) each of the previous five financial years.

reply.p: Following tables contain information on provision starts for the main welfare-to-work schemes for the last six financial years. It should be noted that information on every welfare-to-work scheme is not collected centrally and doing so would incur disproportionate costs. Therefore the following data only covers the key welfare-to-work schemes.
Welfare-to-work schemes have been split into three categories; Intensive support; Less intensive support; and Jobcentre Plus led.

reply.p: This is an operational matter for the Audit Commission and I have asked the chief executive of the Audit Commission to respond to my hon. Friend direct.
